# Performance & Scalability

## Code splitting (established)

- All main pages lazy-loaded in `AppRoutes.tsx` with `Suspense` fallback.
- New pages **must** use `lazy(() => import(...))` + `withSuspense`.

## Data fetching

- Use **server pagination** via `getTableData` / `useTableDataQuery`—do not fetch entire datasets when API supports pagination.
- Default Query `staleTime: 30s`—avoid redundant refetches; override only when needed.
- Polling: use sparingly (`refetchInterval`); disable when tab/feature inactive.
- Invalidate narrowly (`tableRoot`, specific `get` path)—not global cache clears.

## Renders

- No automatic `memo` / `useCallback`—add only when profiling shows benefit.
- Avoid oversized Context values that change every render and re-render the tree.
- Keep page state local; lift only when multiple children need it.

## Bundle hygiene

- Import MUI icons individually (`@mui/icons-material/Search`)—already the pattern.
- Do not import entire lodash-style libraries for one function.

## DataGrid / lists

- Server `paginationMode="server"` with correct `rowCount`.
- Consider virtualization only when measured performance issue exists (MUI DataGrid has built-in virtualization).

## Scalability without over-engineering

- Add a new `*Service.ts` + `hooks/services/use*.ts` per domain—do not build generic meta-frameworks.
- Extract shared code when **second** legitimate use appears—not before.

## Build

- Output dir: `build/` for Firebase Hosting deploy workflow.
- Run `npm run build` after significant changes—catches TS errors via `tsc`.

## Images & assets

- Optimize large static images before adding to `assets/images/`.
- Prefer SVG icons from existing sets.
